about.summary: Package for drawing calibrated scales with tick marks on (non-orthogonal) variable vectors in scatterplots and biplots. Also provides some functions for multivariate analysis such principal coordinate analysis.

name: r-calibrate
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.7.5' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-calibrate
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/calibrate_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/calibrate/calibrate_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 33f4f6874f0a979af3ce592ed1105e829d3df1fbf05c6e0cd3829a13b21d82e8

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mass

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('calibrate')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('calibrate')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=calibrate
  license: GPL-2
  summary: Package for drawing calibrated scales with tick marks on (non-orthogonal) variable
    vectors in scatterplots and biplots. Also provides some functions for multivariate
    analysis such principal coordinate analysis.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), MASS
# Description: Package for drawing calibrated scales with tick marks on (non-orthogonal) variable vectors in scatterplots and biplots. Also provides some functions for multivariate analysis such principal coordinate analysis.
# License: GPL-2

# Repository: CRAN

put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
